Review_body:
There is not enough money in the universe to get Daniel Craig and Angelina Jolie to make another one of these films. This is just embarrassing. The plot, the effects, the music, the writing - this should have been a Nicolas Cage direct-to-video film. Every bad action movie cliche can be seen in this farce. Bullets that do no damage (and rarely hit their target), ridiculous made-up artifacts with special powers, a guy with a fedora (really, there's a guy with a fedora), a woman that lives in a temple and has no real job and limitless money, etc, etc...Angelina Jolie is beautiful, sexy, pouty, she wears sexy outfits with a padded bra (yeah, they really put her in a padded bra), she performs acrobatic stunts, she has a shower scene (with no nudity), and she stars in this really bad movie, so none of those positive things matter.This movie does everyting wrong, all the way down to billing Jon Voight as a lead actor when he isn't even in the first hour. Terrible film... just terrible.RealReview Posting Scoring Criteria:
